<font size="1">SEA SuperSession: </font><br>
<font class="subhead">Outfitting The Digital Consumer-Part One</font><br>
<font class="subhead2">Sunday, January 7, 11:30 am-12:00 pm, Room: LVCC N257</font></p>

This is certainly the year of the digital 
consumer whether you are rewinding live TV with your PVR or listening to digital 
music as you stroll through the park. Consumers are connected everywhere, anytime and it's only 
getting better. Whether you digitize your home, office or car, you will see that technology is 
affordable and it's getting easier and easier to use. 
Robin Raskin, editor-in-chief of FamilyPC magazine, will demonstrate some of the best new digital devices, 
show you how they work and how they will affect you.<p>

<b><u>Moderator</u>:</b>

<table><tr><td>
<img src="images/Raskin.jpg" border="0">
</td><td valign="bottom"><font size="-1">
